  <description>Technicians Don Johnson and John Spencer examine the Kevatron, a special type of atom smasher used to produce nuclear fission in the lighter elements. Costing only $10,000, the Kevatron proves its worth by producing nuclear particles equal to those produced by $450,000 worth of radium, the original atomic element. The Kevatron is just another of the interesting sights in the scientific sideshow at the University of Chicago's new research center.</description>
